Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.31,0:00:18.34,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}I have a big gun, I took it from my Lord...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.55,0:00:21.79,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}Sick with Justice, I just wanna feel you...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.02,0:00:25.20,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}I'm your angel, only a ring away...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.32,0:00:28.55,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}You make me violate you, no matter who you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.53,0:00:38.67,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}It's all up to you, no one lives forever...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.87,0:00:42.26,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}Been burn in the hell, by all those pigs out there...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.34,0:00:45.53,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}It's always been hell, from when I was born...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.67,0:00:48.72,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}They make me violate them, no matter who they are!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.72,0:00:52.26,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3\fs79}Get down on your knees! Get a good head on your shoulders!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.26,0:00:55.69,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}If it's for your guys, go to the end of the Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.69,0:00:59.00,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}Do what you think, give it with dedication...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.00,0:01:02.27,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}I'll put out your misery!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.36,0:01:05.67,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}You made a mess! For Christ sakes, this rotten world!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.67,0:01:09.10,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}Shit out of luck! Go with my vision!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.10,0:01:12.54,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}Light up the fire! Right on the power!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.54,0:01:15.90,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}Weapon... I have it all!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.94,0:01:24.48,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}Weapon... I have it all!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.26,0:01:40.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The sea's so calm today.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.50,0:01:44.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The waters around here\Ncan be really technicolor.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.17,0:01:47.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dive in, and you're\Ntreated to a masterpiece.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.07,0:01:51.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure it is. I did a little scuba\Ndiving long ago at Ishigaki Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.51,0:01:55.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It sounds privileged. Like the\Nfruitful life of a bachelor yuppie.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.22,0:01:58.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't that great.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.35,0:02:02.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Drinking beer while feeling this sea\Nbreeze on my skin is far more privileged.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.59,0:02:17.05,Black Lagoon German Titles,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(170,170)\pos(960,1056)}_______________\NNaval base at Kiel, 1945
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.91,0:02:25.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So it's "Farewell Germany".
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.88,0:02:28.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a shame that the last glimpse\NI get of the German sky...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.45,0:02:30.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...is of its usual leaden color.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.92,0:02:34.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to that, the Allies'\Npatrol over us has thinned.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.79,0:02:37.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once we get past the Shetlands\Nand out of the North Sea...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.36,0:02:41.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...we'll soon be under Spain's blue\Nsky, and then on to Africa's beaches.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.09,0:02:45.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll soon be longing for some\Nclouds, Lieutenant Colonel Matsuto.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.33,0:02:49.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right. As a man here to\Nstudy aeronautics...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.30,0:02:52.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I can't afford to be killed\Nby a plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.71,0:02:55.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not after coming all\Nthe way here to Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.51,0:03:00.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems like we'll understand\Neach other on this long trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.78,0:03:04.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to feel the same about\Nthat other passenger as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.12,0:03:11.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just don't understand them.\NThose men, the SS and SD's.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.90,0:03:24.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Darn. I really did\Nhave a privileged life.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.31,0:03:31.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A little problem with the car, and\Nlife takes a sudden nosedive here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.45,0:03:35.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Lun, is that new? How much?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.88,0:03:40.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's too much. I'll bet it's stolen.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.62,0:03:47.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, well. It's not like anyone has\Nanything to spare in their wallets.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.60,0:03:54.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd better pass. I can just hear\NRevy labeling me a softie again.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.32,0:04:07.95,Black Lagoon German Titles 2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(220,0)\fs80\pos(960,1004)}__________\NNear the Cape Verde Islands,\NAfrica, 1945
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.49,0:04:18.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Check.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.33,0:04:26.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gentlemen, we can look forward\Nto sea turtle soup tonight!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.44,0:04:36.65,Black Lagoon German Titles,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(190,210)\fs85\pos(958,960)}__________\NThe Indian Ocean
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.21,0:04:38.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're moving with us at bearing 270.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.18,0:04:41.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a freighter out of South\NAfrica heading to Ceylon.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.05,0:04:43.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.55,0:04:47.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're in battle positions.\NPlease get inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.19,0:04:51.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I apologize, but I want\Nyou to answer me one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.22,0:04:56.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you going to ignore your\Norders and attack that freighter?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.33,0:04:58.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What shall we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.63,0:05:01.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will get you to Batavia\Nwithout fail Lieutenant Colonel.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.73,0:05:02.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fritz.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.54,0:05:03.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.47,0:05:06.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you incapable of even greeting\Nthe enemy without confirmation?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.14,0:05:09.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And yet you consider\Nyourself this ship's...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.54,0:05:10.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Very well, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.71,0:05:12.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have them hurry with the loading\Nof the torpedo under maintenance.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.15,0:05:16.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You too, Lieutenant Colonel, get inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.12,0:05:19.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An attack would be a\Ncompletely unnecessary risk.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.15,0:05:22.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is a transport of your\Nlong-life enemy, England.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.92,0:05:27.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's being carried is fuel\Nfor an invasion...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.66,0:05:29.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...of the ally we'll soon\Nbe guests of.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.36,0:05:32.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're telling me to ignore that enemy?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.73,0:05:36.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying there was no point\Nin our fighting this war so far?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.97,0:05:43.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At this stage, sinking that ship will\Nhave no effect on our fatherland.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.01,0:05:46.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.75,0:05:48.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.62,0:05:55.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying that we\Ncannot stop the inevitable?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.99,0:05:58.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you trying to force me to say more?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.39,0:06:01.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. I just didn't expect\Nto hear what you said.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.83,0:06:06.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you were worrying about\Nsomething more meaningless.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.60,0:06:11.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I apologize. Despite that, there are\Nstill battles that you must take on.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.50,0:06:15.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go. Prepare the\Ntorpedoes for surface attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.91,0:06:18.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll credit this ship with its 31st hit.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.48,0:06:24.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Launcher is ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.38,0:06:28.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, let's go! We will keep fighting!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.19,0:06:34.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you going to go drinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.93,0:06:36.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go. As soon as\NI'm finished calculating...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.83,0:06:38.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...the fuel efficiency of the\Ntorpedo ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.86,0:06:40.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good job.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.43,0:06:42.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.47,0:06:44.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I dunno.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.84,0:06:47.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do I look like an off-season Santa?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.74,0:06:49.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,During the day, you were looking\Ninto a shop, weren't you, Rock?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.28,0:06:52.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? N-No, that was...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.34,0:06:54.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you just tell me\Nwhen you want something?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.88,0:06:58.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait. Then you mean, that's for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.56,0:07:09.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The enemy ship just passed over us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.51,0:07:16.72,Black Lagoon German Titles 2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs83\fad(215,240)\pos(960,990)}_______\NNear the Nicobar Islands, Indonesia
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.89,0:07:22.35,Black Lagoon German Titles 3,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(960,1078)\fad(215,240)}__________\NMarch 25, 1945
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.71,0:07:29.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Set course to two-zero-zero.\NWe'll get behind the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.22,0:07:34.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we turn twice we can get behind them.\NThe second turn will be in four minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.05,0:07:36.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good. We'll go with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.56,0:07:41.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're detecting sound from another\Nvessel in front of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.99,0:07:43.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! Yet another signal!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.76,0:07:45.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The enemy's coming out in numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.77,0:07:50.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We are about to be subjugated,\Nwith Batavia right in front of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.40,0:07:54.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not yet, gentlemen.\NBoth engines full power.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.11,0:07:56.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Set course to one-seven-zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.31,0:07:57.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One-seven-zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.28,0:07:59.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fire the Zigarren astern.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.65,0:08:00.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Firing Zigarren.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.75,0:08:10.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One of the enemy ships is moving away.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.29,0:08:15.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They took the bait. Stop\Nthe ship. Silent running.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.07,0:08:26.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One ship is staying right\Nwith us, and won't break away.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.74,0:08:31.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's active sonar!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.64,0:08:32.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Full power to the engines!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.58,0:08:34.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Port 20 degrees! To depth of 40!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.00,0:08:54.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the forward torpedo room! We're\Ntaking on water! We've lost control!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.47,0:08:58.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Close the fore hatch!\NCaptain! Please take care!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.04,0:09:09.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've stopped taking on water,\Nbut we can't blow the main tank.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.82,0:09:14.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Engines and the electric generator\Nare damaged beyond repair.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.76,0:09:21.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is unfortunate that we couldn't\Nreturn the Japanese to his homeland.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.66,0:09:24.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lieutenant Colonel Matsuto\Nhas already...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.83,0:09:28.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The way of a samurai.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.27,0:09:30.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't realize he had brought\Na sword on board for that reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.47,0:09:38.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Brave and loyal soldiers\Nof the German navy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.91,0:09:43.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We faced great opposition and\Nrough waters in the Atlantic...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.02,0:09:48.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...but we will finish our final battle,\Nwithout seeing the coconuts of Batavia.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.06,0:09:54.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our ship is currently run\Naground at a depth of 57 meters.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.43,0:09:56.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Both our engines and\Nballast are beyond repair.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.53,0:10:00.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have endured numerous\Nbattles with courage.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.87,0:10:04.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At this moment I relieve\Nyou all of military duties.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.44,0:10:07.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We will run out of air in about two hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.87,0:10:10.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You may each choose\Nhow you wish to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.11,0:10:15.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lieutenant Colonel, I have to talk to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.98,0:10:20.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Captain, I haven't heard the\Nengine running for some time now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.55,0:10:21.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When will we surface?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.65,0:10:26.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As it turns out, we won't\Nbe surfacing. Ever again.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.66,0:10:29.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.83,0:10:32.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're worthless.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.56,0:10:33.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.67,0:10:36.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't get it. You just\Ndon't get it, do you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.94,0:10:37.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get what?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.07,0:10:39.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The importance of your mission!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.94,0:10:43.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have any idea what significance\Nthis painting I'm transporting has?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.34,0:10:47.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, so the package was this painting.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.08,0:10:50.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't look like anything\Nof great significance to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.65,0:10:53.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is its title?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.39,0:10:55.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Twelve Knights led by Brunhilda."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.76,0:11:02.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen! This is the only tableau\Npainted since the Fuhrer took power.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.00,0:11:07.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Steadfast in our honor and loyalty,\Nhide this until the promised day.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.10,0:11:11.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the day the Nazi flag flies again...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.14,0:11:16.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...this will be the guiding light for\Nour comrades who have scattered!"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.61,0:11:21.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, you already know we\Nare going to lose this war.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.71,0:11:25.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you wanted to prepare\Nfor the next war.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.62,0:11:28.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You people make me sick!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.76,0:11:32.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have family?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.96,0:11:36.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A wife and child in Stuttgart. So what?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.10,0:11:42.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am proud that I fought with\Nall I had for my country.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.27,0:11:46.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no regrets, even now as I\Nam destined to rot in the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.04,0:11:49.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, if there is one dissatisfaction...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.81,0:11:54.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...it is the fact that I have to share\Na casket with a bastard like you...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.25,0:11:58.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...who won't bother to remember his\Nfamily, even in his last moments.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.22,0:12:01.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take back that remark, Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.59,0:12:04.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You cannot compare family to the\Nrighteousness of our country!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.32,0:12:08.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's worthless. No\Nmatter how you struggle...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.99,0:12:11.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...the empire of the corporal, whose\Npaintings won't sell, is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.33,0:12:13.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.33,0:12:17.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By tolerating your delusions, look what's\Nbecome of my country and my navy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.24,0:12:19.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.40,0:12:23.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd say it was worth sinking, if\Nbecause of it, my children will never...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.21,0:12:26.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...have to see that\Naccursed Nazi flag again.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.05,0:12:28.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up! Take it back!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.15,0:12:33.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It could very well be God's\Nwill for our ship to sink here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.13,0:12:43.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.93,0:12:46.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I shouldn't have opened\Nmy mouth about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.53,0:12:50.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I only went scuba diving\Nonce, at Ishigaki Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.37,0:12:53.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dutch tricked me into this!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.87,0:12:57.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's all you've said since we left port!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.88,0:13:00.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be a little more interesting, you idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.81,0:13:06.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way I'm capable\Nof doing this salvaging!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.27,0:13:15.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, I explained it\Nbriefly at the office...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.84,0:13:19.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...but I'll go through the details again\Nbefore we go in. Benny, will you start?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.75,0:13:23.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. First, take a look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.92,0:13:27.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An old story from half a century ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.79,0:13:29.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Some nostalgic talk by\Nsome elderly gentleman.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.62,0:13:33.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,IXC-type attack submarine\NU-1324 of the German navy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.96,0:13:36.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A submarine in the Wolf Pack\Nthat tore up the Atlantic.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.90,0:13:40.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The captain was Major Venztel H. Ahbe.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.07,0:13:44.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The last order he received\Nfrom his falling homeland...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.37,0:13:48.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...was to take an officer of\Nthe Japanese navy to Batavia.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.11,0:13:52.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But things weren't that simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.81,0:13:55.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To get there they had to go from\NKiel in Europe, around Cape Agulhas...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.55,0:13:58.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and then past the Indian Ocean.\NIt's a voyage worthy of Magellan.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.32,0:14:01.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Ahbe pulled it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.76,0:14:04.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But when he could finally\Nsee his destination...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.73,0:14:09.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...his ship and passenger\Nsuddenly ran out of luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.96,0:14:13.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,While searching for the Japanese, the\NU.S. Navy came across this U-boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.83,0:14:16.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Having nothing else to do, they\Nall decided to strike at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.31,0:14:20.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The poor U-1324 finally\Nran out of strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.17,0:14:24.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The captain and 44 of his\Ncrew disappeared...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.14,0:14:26.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...into the darkness of the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.65,0:14:33.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Up to this point, that's historical fact,\Nbut there is another, untold story.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.02,0:14:35.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A story about an SS officer...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.16,0:14:37.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...who appeared from Kiel Port\Nthe night before departure...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.39,0:14:43.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...forcing his way on board with\Npapers from the secret police.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.73,0:14:46.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take a look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.27,0:14:51.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the painting he\Nheld on to for dear life.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.47,0:14:54.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The artist is August\NJanke, an unknown painter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.31,0:14:59.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The title is "The Twelve\NKnights Led by Brunhilda".
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.41,0:15:02.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a boring painting.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.18,0:15:06.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even graffiti on the New York\NMetro is more appealing than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.59,0:15:09.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did an SS officer board\Na submarine with no gold...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.89,0:15:12.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...no secret documents, but\Njust a single painting?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.00,0:15:19.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't give it too much thought.\NIt's just an incredible story.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.70,0:15:22.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no explanation\Nfor the reason behind it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.17,0:15:26.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The one thing that we know\Nis that this painting...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.21,0:15:28.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...is sleeping in a sunken submarine.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.74,0:15:32.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've been hired by an\Nantique collector in Spain.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.48,0:15:35.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His hobby is collecting the artwork\Nof artists from the Nazi era.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.98,0:15:37.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The guy's got a weird hobby.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.92,0:15:42.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn right. Most of Janke's work\Nwas burnt in war disasters.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.82,0:15:47.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He had completely given up on it,\Nand the U-boat long ago. But...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.69,0:15:51.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, last year a French phone company\Nlaying down underwater cables...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.40,0:15:55.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...discovered U-1324.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.10,0:15:58.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And they found that there\Nwasn't much water inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.07,0:16:02.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Several countries are fighting over the\Ncontrol of water territories in this area.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.28,0:16:08.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No one can make a go for it easily.\NAnd that's where we come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.88,0:16:11.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A nice 50,000 dollar job, plus expenses.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.42,0:16:15.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, here are the steps for\Nthe job. Take a look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.62,0:16:20.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The French found that the bow\Nend is completely flooded.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.73,0:16:24.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The two of you will go in through\Nthe torpedo tubes and then shut them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.40,0:16:28.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once you weld the hole shut, you should\Nbe able to open the door in the interior.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.94,0:16:29.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Weld?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.00,0:16:31.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do we do to get out?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.24,0:16:34.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just make a hole in the\Nsubmarine's body and swim out.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.24,0:16:37.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once we get what we want outta\Nthere, who cares what happens to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.75,0:16:41.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right then, let's get this over with.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.25,0:16:45.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've never even done weekend carpentry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.55,0:16:50.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And we're doing this all underwater.\NI can't imagine how it'll work.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.89,0:16:53.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, are you done\Nchecking the equipment?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.59,0:16:56.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you keep talking nonsense, I'll\Nthrow you into the sea without a tank.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.03,0:17:00.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm mostly done.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.30,0:17:01.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about the\Nbuoyancy compensator?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.50,0:17:03.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you test the gauge?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.37,0:17:05.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you end up drowning I'm\Ngonna leave you down there...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.41,0:17:07.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...in that casket, with those Nazi guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.74,0:17:10.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be so difficult. I'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.08,0:17:15.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you die you'd be causing me trouble!\NSo stop talking back, you idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.18,0:17:17.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Revy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.18,0:17:19.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once you dive I'll only be able\Nto track you with the beacon.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.82,0:17:21.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful not to use up the batteries.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.86,0:17:23.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.82,0:17:27.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And this. A souvenir from Balalaika\Nwhen she returned from her country.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.66,0:17:30.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An underwater rifle?\NDoes it have full-auto?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.53,0:17:33.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course. Take it as a protective charm.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.94,0:17:38.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. Let's go. Follow me, Rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.38,0:17:47.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you won her over with\Na gun and saved Rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.75,0:17:50.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've got a lot of tricks up your sleeve.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.65,0:17:55.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You could say that. As an employer\NI've gotta deal with human relations.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.16,0:18:05.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The beacon's been activated.\NThe PLRS is working fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.60,0:18:07.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}All right.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.67,0:18:10.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're headed straight\Nfor the metal body.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.14,0:18:12.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Revy sure seems used\Nto this kind of thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.44,0:18:16.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course she is. I wouldn't\Nhave hired her solely on her...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.34,0:18:22.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...skill with guns. She's got natural\Ntalent when it comes to swimming.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.56,0:18:38.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Dutch?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.53,0:18:39.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's up?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.87,0:18:41.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come up here for a second.\NThere's a ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.97,0:18:42.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.77,0:18:45.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're not on a regular sea route.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.51,0:18:47.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The cable company's about the only\None I can imagine coming here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.17,0:18:50.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cable company? It can't be.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.41,0:18:53.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been listening to their\Ncommunications...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.08,0:18:54.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...ever since we got the offer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.88,0:18:57.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They shouldn't be out here\Nfor another three days.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.52,0:18:59.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, that's a research ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.59,0:19:02.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look. It's got some large\Nequipment on the back.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.19,0:19:07.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't amusing. Put\Nup a Thai navy flag.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.36,0:19:08.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.93,0:19:15.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}To the stopped ship. This is the{\i0}\N{\i1}White Heather. Please respond.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.10,0:19:18.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They wanna communicate.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.34,0:19:22.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is PT377 of the Thai navy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.24,0:19:25.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We are currently on a mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.45,0:19:27.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'd like to inquire about\Nyour purpose in this area.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.45,0:19:31.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell us your nationality,\Nship number and signal code.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.12,0:19:35.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We see that you are acting{\i0}\N{\i1}independently.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.42,0:19:36.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Where is your mother ship?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.62,0:19:39.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is a military matter\Nand I cannot answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.33,0:19:43.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I request your information\None more time, over.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.67,0:19:51.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They sure are demanding.\NThey're not normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.17,0:19:54.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going back to the control room.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.21,0:19:56.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Keep track of them, and\Ntell me everything you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.24,0:19:59.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've got some unusual cloud\Nactivity. Fold up your umbrella.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.18,0:20:02.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right. What'll we do about those two?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.45,0:20:04.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As long as their beacon is on,\Nwe can pick them up any time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.19,0:20:07.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Worst case scenario, we blast these\Nguys and then pick the two up.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.22,0:20:10.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hail Uberfuhrer!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.36,0:20:14.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Upon checking communications\Nthrough radio interception...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.36,0:20:16.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...just as we suspected there are no\Nnavy vessels of any nation in this area.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.50,0:20:19.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore, we conclude that\Nthey are hated bandits...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.17,0:20:21.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...who are plundering\Nthis sacred grave site.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.50,0:20:24.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your decision please, Commander.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.04,0:20:27.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They are such fools.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.17,0:20:30.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The proof of inheritance of this\Ngrave site is rightfully ours.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.08,0:20:35.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Very well, Squad Commander. I will\Nallow destruction with an iron fist.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.35,0:20:39.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.72,0:20:41.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Dutch. There's movement.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.75,0:20:44.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. I just started the engines.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.49,0:20:48.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What in the world are they doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.60,0:20:57.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dutch! They have TOWs!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.01,0:21:01.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it! I should've guessed\Nthat's what they'd do!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.61,0:21:04.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hang on, Benny!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.82,0:21:11.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.89,0:21:13.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anti-tank missiles!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.32,0:21:16.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Run, run, degenerates.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.96,0:21:21.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is our destined reunion with\NBrunhilda. No one will stop us.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.81,0:21:35.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This underground grave is about to open.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.50,0:23:18.50,Black Lagoon Next Episode,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur10\pos(980,916)}Next Episode
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.37,0:23:21.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll no longer be one of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.71,0:23:24.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When that happens, I'm gonna kill you.
